t-style: italic; font-weight: bold;">    </span><span style="font-style: italic;"><b>    </b><span style="font-style: italic;">Starting VMware Tools services in the virtual machine:</span></span></div><div><span style="font-style: italic;"> <span>    <span>    </span></span>  Switching to guest configuration:                                   done</span></div><div><span style="font-style: italic;"> <span>    <span>    </span></span>  Guest memory manager:                                            <font color="#ff2600">  failed</font></span></div><div><span style="font-style: italic;"/><span style="font-style: italic;">     <span>    </span>  Guest operating system daemon:                                      done</span></div><div>Step 4: =&gt; sudo /usr/local/etc/rc.d/vmware-tools.sh <font color="#941100">status</font></div><div>                  <i> vmtoolsd is<font color="#009051"> running</font></i></div><div>Any way don’t expect too much from the VMtools !!!</div></en-note>
